label.value: resting state functional magnetic resonance image data set

definition.value: A type of functional MRI in which the participant is not given a task, but just rests during acquisision

label.value: task-based functional magnetic resonance image data set

definition.value: A type of functional MRI in which the participant is given a task or tasks, which are timed with the acquisition

label.value: perfusion weighted magnetic resonance image data set

definition.value: An magnetic resonance image data set that captures volume and flow of blood in the brain.

label.value: proton density magnetic resonance image data set

definition.value: An magnetic resonance image data set in which the contrast emphasizes density of protons, supressing T1 and T2 effects

label.value: T1 weighted magnetic resonance image data set

definition.value: An magnetic resonance image acquired using a T1 weighted magnetic resonance image acquisition sequence.

label.value: post-Gd T1 weighted magnetic resonance image data set

definition.value: A T1 weighted image data set where gadolidium contrast agent has been administered to the participant before image acquistion.

label.value: T1 weighted GRE magnetic resonance image data set

definition.value: T1 weighted image data set collected using a gradient recall echo sequence.

label.value: high resolution T1 weighted magnetic resonance image data set

definition.value: A T1-weighted image data set acquired from an NMR/MRI machine with at least a 3 Tesla magnet and in which the voxel size is isotropic.

label.value: baseline high resolution T1 weighted magnetic resonance image data set

definition.value: A T1w image data set collected at an evaluant's first visit in a study.

label.value: follow-up high resolution T1 weighted magnetic resonance image data set

definition.value: A T1w image data set collected at a later time than the evaluant's first scan.

label.value: T1 weighted SE magnetic resonance image data set

definition.value: A T1 weighted image data set acquired using a spin echo sequence.

label.value: T2 weighted magnetic resonance image data set

definition.value: A magnetic resonance image produced by a T2 weighted magnetic resonance image acquisition sequence.

label.value: T2 weighted FLAIR magnetic resonance image data set

definition.value: A T2 weighted image data set collected using a FLAIR sequence.

label.value: T2 weighted FSE  magnetic resonance image data set

definition.value: T2 weighted image collected using a fast/turbo spin echo sequence.

label.value: T2 weighted SE magnetic resonance image data set

definition.value: A type of T2-weighted image in which the acquisition is performed using a 2D spin-echo technique

label.value: T2 weighted STIR magnetic resonance image data set

definition.value: A T2 weighted magnetic resonance image data set collected using a STIR sequence to suppress the signal coming from fat.

label.value: T2* weighted GRE magnetic resonance image data set

definition.value: T2* weighted image data set collected using a gradient echo sequence.

label.value: raw magnetic resonance image data set

definition.value: An image data set that is the direct output of an magnetic resonance imaging assay and whose values encode spatial frequencies produced by the NMR or MRI instrument.

label.value: image data set analysis

definition.value: The process of deriving a data item from an image data set using computer algorithms. The produced data item can be an image data set, data measurement, or any other data item.

label.value: raw magnetic resonance image data set reconstruction

definition.value: A process that transforms raw magnetic resonance image data from an NMR/MRI machine into a reconstructed magnetic resonance image data set.

label.value: brain region atlas image data set

definition.value: An image data set consisting of values computed from multiple image data sets encoded to represent the spatial location of individual functional or structural regions of a canonical brain.

label.value: probabilistic brain region atlas image dataset

definition.value: A brain atlas consisting of weighted values that respresent the probability that a voxel X is part of some brain component Y, typically derived from multiple image data sets.

label.value: deterministic brain region atlas image data set

definition.value: A brain atlas consisting of discrete integer values where a value X denotes a voxel is part of some brain component Y.

label.value: image segmentation map

definition.value: An image data set of integer values in which each value corresponds to some shared characteristic or computed property. The values often belong to a group of pixels or voxels that share the same characteristic, such as a tissue type or anatomical region.

label.value: lesion mask

definition.value: An image data set where voxel intensity values greater than zero encode the location of some brain lesion and voxels outside the lesion have an intensity value of zero.

label.value: T1 lesion mask

definition.value: A lesion mask where the lesions are derived from a T1 weighted image data set.

label.value: T2 FLAIR lesion mask

definition.value: A lesion mask where the lesions are derived from a T2 FLAIR image data set.

label.value: milk assay datum

definition.value: A data item that is the specified output of a milk assay.

label.value: organism diagnostic process

definition.value: A drawing a conclusion based on data that involves the interpretation of data about a given organism (human, animal, or plant) and the assertion to the effect that the organism has or had a disease, disorder, or syndrome of a certain type, or none of these as output.

label.value: diagnosis of an organism

definition.value: A conclusion based on data about that an organism has a disease, disorder, or syndrome of a certain type, or none of these.

label.value: detection technique

definition.value: An assay (A) that is part of another assay (B), where the target entities of A and B are disjoint, and the target entity of A is a proxy for the target of assay B.

label.value: assay kit

definition.value: A device that consists of reagents and devices that enable the performance of a specific type of assay, which could, in addition, require specific instruments not included in the kit.

label.value: epitope specific XCL1 release by T cells

definition.value: A biological process where T cells produce XCL1 resulting from the recognition of a T cell epitope.

label.value: assay measuring epitope specific lymphotactin production by T cells

definition.value: A T cell epitope specific cytokine production assay that detects lymphotactin production by T cells.

label.value: ELISA measuring epitope specific lymphotactin production by T cells

definition.value: An enzyme-linked immunosorbent assay that detects lymphotactin production by T cells.

label.value: remote patient assessment

definition.value: An organism diagnostic process which involves a remote assessment of a patient by a clinician.

label.value: placental blood specimen

definition.value: A specimen that is derived from placental blood.

label.value: placental blood microbiology assay

definition.value: A blood microbiology assay that detects microorganisms in a placental blood specimen.

label.value: placental blood microbiology datum

definition.value: An organism detection datum that is the specified output of a placental blood microbiology assay.

label.value: eukaryota in placental blood datum

definition.value: A placental blood microbiology datum that is about eukaryota.

label.value: synaptosome preparation process

definition.value: A material component separation process where a synaptic terminal is isolated from a neuron by mild homogenization of nervous tissue under isotonic conditions and subsequent fractionation using differential and density gradient centrifugation.

label.value: Illumina HiSeq 1500

definition.value: A DNA sequencer which is manufactured by the Illumina corporation, with a single flow cell. Built upon sequencing by synthesis technology, the machine employs dual surface imaging and offers two high-output options and one rapid-run option.

label.value: NextSeq 550

definition.value: A DNA sequencer manufactured by the Illumina corporation, which provides the increased flexibility of microarray scanning in addition to sequencing.

label.value: Agilent-026655 Whole Mouse Genome Microarray 4x44K v2

definition.value: A DNA microarray manufactured with Agilent 60-mer SurePrint Technology .The SurePrint G3 Mouse Gene Expression 4x44K v2 Microarray provide full coverage of the mouse transcriptome using the latest annotation databases, including long non-coding RNA(lncRNA). Each glass slide is formatted with four high-definition 44K arrays.

label.value: Agilent-030493 SurePrint G3 Mouse Exon 4x180K Microarray

definition.value: A DNA microarray manufactured with Agilent 60-mer SurePrint Technology for studying exon-level gene expression changes. The SurePrint G3 Mouse Exon 4x180K Microarray include probes targeting individual exons. Each glass slide formatted with four 180K arrays.

label.value: Agilent-074809 SurePrint G3 Mouse GE v2 8x60K Microarray

definition.value: A DNA microarray manufactured with Agilent 60-mer SurePrint technology which provides comprehensive coverage of genes and transcripts using the latest annotation databases. The SurePrint G3 Mouse Gene Expression 8x60K v2 Microarray features complete coverage of established RefSeq coding transcripts (NM) from the latest build and updated long non-coding RNA (lncRNA) content to ensure relevant research.Each glass slide formatted with eight high-definition 60K arrays.

label.value: Affymetrix Mouse Genome 430 2.0 Array

definition.value: A DNA microarray manufactured by Affymetrix, which includes complete coverage of the GeneChip Mouse Expression Set 430, for analysis of over 39,000 transcripts and variants from more than 34,000 well-characterized mouse genes and UniGene clusters, on a single array. The sequences for this array were selected from GenBank, dbEST, and RefSeq., and sequence clusters cretaed from the UniGene database.

label.value: Affymetrix Mouse Genome 430A 2.0 Array

definition.value: A DNA microarray manufactured by Affymetrix for gene expression analysis focusing on approximately 14,000 well-characterized genes in the transcribed mouse genome using single-array cartridge. Sequences used in the design of the array were selected from GenBank, dbEST, and RefSeq. The sequence clusters were created from the UniGene database.

label.value: Affymetrix Mouse Gene 1.0 ST Array

definition.value: A DNA microarray manufactured by Affymetrix, which is a whole-transcript array that includes probes to measure both messenger (mRNA) and long intergenic non-coding RNA transcripts (lincRNA). This whole-transcript array design provides a complete expression profile of mRNA as well as the intermediary lincRNA transcripts that impact the mRNA expression profile.

label.value: Affymetrix Mouse Gene 2.1 ST Array

definition.value: A DNA microarray manufactured by Affymetrix, which is a whole-transcript array that includes probes to measure both messenger (mRNA) and long intergenic non-coding RNA transcripts (lincRNA).To supplement the lincRNA data contained in RefSeq, we used sequence and transcript data from lncRNA db.
